\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>Pinko Pallino \\u00e8 il nostro vino  ros\\u00e9 che viene prodotto da uve Sangiovese di prima vendemmia con l\'aggiunta di mosto di salasso prodotto dalla pressatura del nostro vino Gigi\\u00f2 (effettuando un salasso del mosto di Gigi\\u00f2 si ottiente una pi\\u00f9 alta concentrazione di questo stesso vino). Si tratta quindi di un ros\\u00e9  di altissima qualit\\u00e0, di un vivissimo colore rosa. E\' un rosato secco e con acidit\\u00e0 persistente nonch\\u00e9 di ottima struttura, di facile e piacevole beva durante una calda giornata di estate. Pinko Pallino viene rilasciato sei mesi dalla vendemmia e viene vinificato in vasche di acciaio. <br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"20\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Vino ros\\u00e9 IGT Toscana \",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese e Teroldego\",\"exposition\":\"Sud\\/Sud ovest\",\"soil\":\"Misto di alberese e galestro\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"Le uve del nostro ros\\u00e9 sono le prime uve ad essere vendemmiate. Il nostro obbiettivo per Pinko Pallino \\u00e8 di vendemmiare  uve meno mature e con tasso di alcol pi\\u00f9 basso. I grappli vengono lasciati interi e pressati immediatamente dopo la vendemmia. Il mosto viene poi lasciato fermentare a bassa temperatura in vasche di acciaio. A seguito della finificazione del nostro vino Gigi\\u00f2 effettuiamo un salasso del mosto e dopo averlo fatto fermentare separatamente lo aggiungiamo alla quantit\\u00e0 di rosato iniziale per poi produrre il nostro ros\\u00e9 Pinko Pallino. Il rosato rimarr\\u00e0 poi in vasche di acciaio per circa 6 mesi a bassa temperatura (dagli 8 ai 10 gradi) fino all\'imbottigliamento.\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:31:35', '2015-04-01 21:31:35', '74a22d45-a3f1-4980-83e8-efd0973b81b5'),
 ('123', '16', '4', '1', 'it', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gigino\",\"slug\":\"gigino\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"56\"],\"23\":[\"18\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p><strong>Vigneto<\\/strong>: Vigneto \\\"La Noce\\\", situato sulla propriet\\u00e0 di POGGIO LA NOCE, Fiesole (provincia di Firenze, Toscana, Italia)<\\/p><p><strong>Altitudine:<\\/strong> Circa 250 metri sul livello del mare<\\/p><p><strong>Esposizione: <\\/strong>sud, sud-ovest<br><\\/p><p><strong>Ettari vigneto:<\\/strong> 5 ettari<\\/p><p><strong>Piantato nel:<\\/strong> Parte nel 2000, parte nel 2007<\\/p><p><strong>Terreno: <\\/strong>Prevalentemente suddiviso in marne calcaree, di strati di alberese e galestro, con abbondante miscela di ghiaia e sassi.<\\/p><p><strong>Stile potatura: <\\/strong>Cordone<br><\\/p><p><strong>Uve: <\\/strong>100% Sangiovese<br><\\/p><p><strong>Vendemmia:<\\/strong> Tipicamente verso fine settembre, inizio ottobre. Le uve vengono accuratamente selezionate da particelle del nostro vigneto che producono un sangiovese di stile classico ed elegante. La raccolta viene eseguita a mano e le uve vengono trasportate immediatamente in cantina per la selezione finale e la vinificazione. <\\/p><p><strong>Vinificazione: <\\/strong>In seguito ad una accuratissima selezione, i grappoli vengono diraspati delicatamente, mantenendo l\'integrit\\u00e0 dei chicchi, e gli stessi chicchi vengono poi individualmente selezionati su un tavolo di cernita, lasciando cos\\u00ec che soltanto l\'uva migliore entri nelle cisterne di fermentazione per Gigino. La fermentazione avviene appunto in cisterne di acciaio con temperatura controllata, assolutamente in modo naturale utilizzando i lieviti indigeni delle stesse uve. <\\/p><p><strong>Invecchiamento: <\\/strong>L\'invecchiamento avviene in botti di rovere da 10hl, per un periodo che va da alcuni mesi ad un massimo di 12 mesi, a seconda dell\'annata. Le nostre botti provengono dalle migliori tonnelerie e sono tipicamente di grana fine con tostatura media. Utilizziamo un misto di botti nuove ed usate per minimizzare la presenza di aromi di legno. In seguito all\'invecchiamento in botti, il vino viene affitano in bottiglia per circa 12 mesi prima di essere rilasciato. <\\/p><p><strong>Bottiglie prodotte: <\\/strong>3000 bottiglie.<\\/p><p><strong>Alcol:<\\/strong> 13% to 14%<\\/p><p><strong>Potenziale di invecchiamento: <\\/strong>da 5 a 10 anni<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p> Gigino pu\\u00f2 essere considerato il gemello di Gigetto, ma con la differenza che Gigino \\u00e8 un Sangiovese in purezza, quindi con nessun tipo di altra variet\\u00e0 di uva aggiunta. Abbiamo creato questo sangiovese perch\\u00e9 nel nostro vigneto ci sono delle particelle di terreno che producono un classico sangiovese, ma con enorme equilibrio, freschezza e soprattutto eleganza. <br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"17\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Gigino \\u00e8 un vino rosso, IGT Toscana\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese in purezza\",\"exposition\":\"sud, sud ovest\",\"soil\":\"Misto di alberese e galestro\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"Le uve del nostro vino Gigino vengono accuratamente selezionate da particelle del nostro vigneto che producono un sangiovese di stile classico ed elegante. In seguito alla selezione fatta sia sui grappoli che sui chicchi, la vinificazione avviene in tini di acciaio con temperatura controllata, e con lieviti indigeni. L\'invecchiamento avviene in botti di rovere da 10 hl per 12 mese circa, con ulteriore affinamento in bottiglia per altri 12 mesi.\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:31:42', '2015-04-01 21:31:42', '56624b52-d86f-4ac8-85a9-0bd385849223'),
 ('124', '22', '4', '1', 'it', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Paonazzo\",\"slug\":\"paonazzo\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"60\"],\"23\":[\"24\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p>Verr\\u00e0 rilasciato a breve!<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>Verr\\u00e0 rilasciato a breve!<\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"23\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Paonazzo vino rosso IGT Toscana\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese e Teroldego\",\"exposition\":\"Sud\\/Sud ovest\",\"soil\":\"Misto di alberese e galestro\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"Verr\\u00e0 rilasciato a breve!\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:32:18', '2015-04-01 21:32:18', '54d4a2e2-e381-4a2f-8433-c5c3b4656d7c'),
 ('125', '9', '4', '1', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gigio\",\"slug\":\"gigio\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"11\"],\"23\":[\"12\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p><strong>Vinyard<\\/strong>: La Noce vineyard on the property of POGGIO LA NOCE, Fiesole (Province of Florence, Tuscany, Italy).<br><\\/p><p><strong>Altitude:<\\/strong> 800 ft elavation, 250 meters above sea level<\\/p><p><strong>Orientation: <\\/strong>South - South West facing<br><\\/p><p><strong>Vineyard Size:<\\/strong> 5 acres<\\/p><p><strong>Year Planted:<\\/strong> Partly in 2000 and partly in 2006<\\/p><p><strong>Soil: <\\/strong>Medium-textured, predominantly calcareous marl breakdown of alberese and galestro strata, with abundant gravel-rocky mixture.<\\/p><p><strong>Training System: <\\/strong>Spur-pruned cordon for the Sangiovese and Guyot for the Teroldego<br><\\/p><p><strong>Grapes: <\\/strong>90% Sangiovese, 10% Teroldego (starting with 2012 vintage).<\\/p><p><strong>Harvest:<\\/strong> Typically end of September to the first ten days of October depending on the seasons for the Sangiovese. The Teroldego grapes tend to ripen earlier and are harvested earlier (around the 20th of September).<\\/p><p>The Gigi\\u00f2 Sangiovese grapes benefit from the most hang time allowing for greater phenological maturity. They are handpicked and brought immediately to the cellar for further selection.<\\/p><p><strong>Vinification: <\\/strong>After careful cluster selection, followed by gentle destemming, the berries fall on the sorting table where they are sorted individually, allowing only the perfect berries to make it into the Gigi\\u00f2 fermentation vat. Fermentation takes place in temperature controlled stainless steel vats and typically occurs naturally using the grapes own indigenous yeasts. Some juice may be \\\"bled off\\\" before fermentation resulting in higher concentration and thus providing the basis for our Ros\\u00e9, Pinko Pallino.<\\/p><p><strong>Ageing: <\\/strong>The wine will age in French oak barriques (225L each) for 12 months to 18 months depending on the year. Our barriques come from some of the best tonneleries in France and are typically fine grain medium toast. We use a mixture of new and used barriques to avoid excessive wood accent. Following the aging in barriques, the wine is further aged in bottle for another year.<\\/p><p><strong>Bottles Produced: <\\/strong>3000 bottles.<\\/p><p><strong>Alcohol:<\\/strong> 13% to 14%<\\/p><p><strong>Potential Cellaring:<\\/strong> 15+ years.<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>Gigi\\u00f2 is the estate\'s first-born and flagship wine. It is a blend of Sangiovese (90%) and Teroldego (10%). Aged for three years before release, it is the product of the most mature and fully developed fruit in the vineyard. We pull all the stops for this wine. And it shows in the glass. It is a complex, age-worthy wine, with deep colors and lively fruits, with persistent acidity and finish. We like to think of it as a wine for meditation.<br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"10\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Red wine IGT Tuscany\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese and Teroldego\",\"exposition\":\"South South West\",\"soil\":\"Mixture of Alberese and Galestro limestones\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"After careful cluster and berry selection vinification occurs in temperature controlled stainless steel vats with indigenous yeast. Ageing occurs in a mix of new and used French oak barriques for 12 to 18 months with further 12 months ageing in bottle.\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:45:08', '2015-04-01 21:45:08', '4e6e026e-cb6e-4db4-ab5f-e0340f490cda'),
 ('126', '13', '4', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gigetto\",\"slug\":\"gigetto\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"57\"],\"23\":[\"15\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p><strong>Vinyard<\\/strong>: La Noce vineyard on the property of POGGIO LA NOCE, Fiesole (Province of Florence, Tuscany, Italy).<\\/p><p><strong>Altitude:<\\/strong> 800 ft elavation, 250 meters above sea level<\\/p><p><strong>Orientation: <\\/strong>South - South West facing<br><\\/p><p><strong>Vineyard Size:<\\/strong> 5 acres<\\/p><p><strong>Year Planted:<\\/strong> Partly in 2000 and partly in 2006<\\/p><p><strong>Soil: <\\/strong>Medium-textured, predominantly calcareous marl breakdown of alberese and galestro strata, with abundant gravel-rocky mixture.<\\/p><p><strong>Training System: <\\/strong>Spur-pruned cordon for the Sangiovese and Guyot for the Teroldego<br><\\/p><p><strong>Grapes: <\\/strong>95% Sangiovese, 5% Terroldego (proportions can change depending on the year\'s growing season and starting from the 2013 vintage)<br><\\/p><p><strong>Harvest:<\\/strong> Typically, around the 20th to the 22nd of September The Gigetto grapes are picked first as we are trying to make a fresh fruit driven final wine. They are picked at optimal maturity level but with less emphasis on concentration. They are handpicked and brought immediately to the cellar for further selection).<\\/p><p><strong>Vinification: <\\/strong>After careful cluster selection, followed by gentle destemming, the berries fall on the sorting table where they are sorted individually allowing only the perfect berries to make it into the Gigetto fermentation vat. Fermentation takes place in temperature controlled stainless steel vats and typically occurs naturally using the grapes own indigenous yeasts. The Sangiovese grapes and Teroldego grapes are each vinified separately so that they may be blended later. Blending decisions will vary depending on the years, with the percentage Teroldego varying between Gigi\\u00f2 and Gigetto.<\\/p><p><strong>Ageing: <\\/strong>The wine will age in oak botti (1000L barrels) for a few months, up to 6 months depending on the year. Our botti come from one of the best Italian tonnelerie and are typically fine grain medium toast. We use a mixture of new and used large size botti to avoid any excessive wood accent. Following the aging in botti, the wine is further aged in bottle for 6 months.<\\/p><p><strong>Bottles Produced: <\\/strong>4000 bottles.<\\/p><p><strong>Alcohol:<\\/strong> 13% to 14%<\\/p><p><strong>Potential Cellaring:<\\/strong> Easily 5 years<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>We think of it as the little brother of Gigi\\u00f2. It is a wine of surprising immediacy, while still offering plenty of experiences to the nose and palate. Gigetto was born out of our own wish to drink a pleasant, genuine wine, yet with exceptional fruit and easier drinkability. Gigetto is released a year earlier than Gigi\\u00f2 and typically ages in large size botte only a few months.<br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"14\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Red wine IGT Tuscany\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese and Teroldego\",\"exposition\":\"South South West\",\"soil\":\"Mixture of Albarese and Galestro limestones\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"The Gigetto grapes are picked first as we are trying to make a fresh fruit driven wine with less emphasis on concentration. After cluster and berry selection, vinification occurs in temperature controlled stainless steel vats with indigenous yeast. Ageing occurs in oak \\\"botti\\\" or large size barrels (1000L) for 3 to 6 months with further 6 month ageing in bottle.\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:45:28', '2015-04-01 21:45:28', '1df40a27-1f16-436c-adff-6f84c02c6bfd'),
 ('127', '16', '4', '1', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gigino\",\"slug\":\"gigino\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"56\"],\"23\":[\"18\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p><strong>Vinyard<\\/strong>: La Noce vineyard on the property of POGGIO LA NOCE, Fiesole (Province of Florence, Tuscany, Italy).<\\/p><p><strong>Altitude:<\\/strong> 800 ft elavation, 250 meters above sea level<\\/p><p><strong>Orientation: <\\/strong>South - South West facing<br><\\/p><p><strong>Vineyard Size:<\\/strong> 5 acres<\\/p><p><strong>Year Planted:<\\/strong> Partly in 2000 and partly in 2006<\\/p><p><strong>Soil: <\\/strong>Medium-textured, predominantly calcareous marl breakdown of alberese and galestro strata, with abundant gravel-rocky mixture.<\\/p><p><strong>Training System: <\\/strong>Spur-pruned cordon<br><\\/p><p><strong>Grapes: <\\/strong>100% Sangiovese<br><\\/p><p><strong>Harvest:<\\/strong> Typically, around the end of September to beginning of October. The grapes are carefully selected from specific segments of the vineyard where the soil yields a very classic elegant style Sangiovese. They are handpicked and brought immediately to the cellar for further selection<\\/p><p><strong>Vinification: <\\/strong>After careful cluster selection, followed by gentle destemming, the berries roll onto the sorting table where they are sorted individually, allowing only the perfect berries to make it into the Gigino fermentation vat. Fermentation takes place in temperature controlled stainless steel vats and typically occurs naturally using the grapes own indigenous yeasts.<\\/p><p><strong>Ageing: <\\/strong>The wine will age in oak botti (1000L barrels) for a few months, up to 12 months depending on the year. Our botti come from one of the best Italian tonnelerie and are typically fine grain medium toast. We use a mixture of new and used large size botti to avoid any excessive wood accent. Following the aging in botti, the wine is further aged in bottle for up to 12 months.<\\/p><p><strong>Bottles Produced: <\\/strong>3000 bottles.<\\/p><p><strong>Alcohol:<\\/strong> 13% to 14%<\\/p><p><strong>Potential Cellaring:<\\/strong> 5 to 10 years<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>This might be considered Gigetto\'s twin brother except for the fact that Gigino is \\\"Sangiovese in purezza\\\", meaning 100% sangiovese, with no blending of other grape varietals. This wine came about because we noticed that some segments of the vineyard were especially well suited for Sangiovese, yielding a very classic style Sangiovese. The Sangiovese fruit from these segments of the vineyard produces a wine with perfect balance, freshness and elegance.<br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"17\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Red Wine IGT Tuscany\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese\",\"exposition\":\"South South West\",\"soil\":\"Mixture of Alberese and Galestro limestones\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"The Gigino grapes are carefully selected from specific segments of the vineyard where the soil yields a very classic elegant style Sangiovese. After cluster and berry selection, vinification occurs in temperature controlled stainless steel vats with indigenous yeast. Ageing occurs in oak \\\"botti\\\" or large size barrels (1000L) for\\u00a012 months with further\\u00a012 month ageing in bottle.\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:45:41', '2015-04-01 21:45:41', 'e8d0f2f7-2120-46cf-88b7-2bd9925051d9'),
 ('128', '19', '4', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Pinko Pallino\",\"slug\":\"pallino\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"59\"],\"23\":[\"21\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p><strong>Vinyard<\\/strong>: La Noce vineyard on the property of POGGIO LA NOCE, Fiesole (Province of Florence, Tuscany, Italy).<\\/p><p><strong>Altitude:<\\/strong> 800 ft elavation, 250 meters above sea level<\\/p><p><strong>Orientation: <\\/strong>South - South West facing<br><\\/p><p><strong>Vineyard Size:<\\/strong> 5 acres<\\/p><p><strong>Year Planted:<\\/strong> Partly in 2000 and partly in 2006<\\/p><p><strong>Soil: <\\/strong>Medium-textured, predominantly calcareous marl breakdown of alberese and galestro strata, with abundant gravel-rocky mixture.<\\/p><p><strong>Training System: <\\/strong>Spur-pruned cordon<br><\\/p><p><strong>Grapes: <\\/strong>100% Sangiovese<br><\\/p><p><strong>Harvest:<\\/strong> Typically, around the middle of September. The Ros\\u00e9 grapes are the first to be harvested and we look to pick grapes with lower maturity level (and less alcohol potential). They are handpicked and brought immediately to the cellar for further selection. <\\/p><p><strong>Vinification: <\\/strong>The grape clusters are pressed whole and immediately. The juice is then left to ferment in a steel vat at cooler temperatures. In parallel some of the bled off juice from Gigi\\u00f2 is also fermented separately. This juice will have had minimal contact with the skins and will therefore remain light colored. When both fermentations will be complete, the two batches will be blended together to build the final Ros\\u00e9 wine.<\\/p><p><strong>Ageing: <\\/strong>The wine will rest in stainless steel vats for a few months again at cooler temperatures (8 to 10 degrees celcius) until it is bottled. It releases roughly 6-9 months later.<\\/p><p><strong>Bottles Produced: <\\/strong>1000 bottles.<\\/p><p><strong>Alcohol:<\\/strong> 12% to 13%<\\/p><p><strong>Acidity (g\\/L):<\\/strong> Depending on the years, in the range of 6 to 7.5<br><\\/p><p><strong>Potential Cellaring:<\\/strong> 5 to 10 years<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>Is a Ros\\u00e9 bottling produced from a blend of both early harvested Sangiovese fruit and the bleeding off part of the juice from the later harvested Gigi\\u00f2 fruit. (Bleeding off some of the Gigi\\u00f2 juice allows us to achieve higher concentration for the Gigi\\u00f2 final wine). The quality of the fruit for this Ros\\u00e9 wine is therefore of the highest quality we produce. It is a gorgeous, radiant pink, grapefruit color, dry, with long acidity and structure, yet very easy to drink on a hot summer day. Pinko Pallino is released just six months after harvest and it is only aged in steel vats.<br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"20\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Ros\\u00e9 Wine IGT Tuscany\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese\",\"exposition\":\"South South West\",\"soil\":\"Mixture of Alberese and Galestro limestones\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"The Ros\\u00e9 grapes are the first to be harvested and we look to pick grapes with lower maturity level and less alcohol potential. The grape clusters are pressed whole immediately. The juice is then left to ferment in a steel vat at cooler temperatures. In parallel some of the bled off juice from Gigi\\u00f2 is also fermented separately. The two batches will then be blended together to build the final Ros\\u00e9 wine. The wine will rest in stainless steel vats for a few months at cooler temperatures (8 to 10 degrees celcius) until it is bottled. It releases roughly 6-9 months later.\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:46:08', '2015-04-01 21:46:08', '37df1d81-b364-47e7-8212-0800dda602b5'),
 ('129', '22', '4', '1', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Paonazzo\",\"slug\":\"paonazzo\",\"postDate\":1421101440,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"22\":[\"60\"],\"23\":[\"24\"],\"24\":\"\",\"14\":\"<p>Coming soon!<\\/p>\",\"13\":\"<p>Coming soon!<br><\\/p>\",\"15\":{\"23\":{\"type\":\"specifications\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"wineType\":\"Red wine IGT Tuscany\",\"vineyardLocation\":\"Poggio La Noce, Fiesole\",\"grapes\":\"Sangiovese and Teroldego\",\"exposition\":\"South South West\",\"soil\":\"Mixture of albarese and galestro limestones\",\"vinificationAndMaturation\":\"Coming soon!\"}}}}}', '2015-04-01 21:46:20', '2015-04-01 21:46:20', 'e2598d99-ee6b-4c9a-8f0d-305f9929dcba'),
 ('130', '42', '3', '1', 'it', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"L\'azienda\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1421257320,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"43\":{\"type\":\"banner\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bannerHeadline\":\"Un piccolo team di professionisiti concentrati sulla produzione di eleganti vini nelle colline di Fiesole\",\"bannerVideo\":\"\",\"bannerImage\":[\"52\"]}}},\"7\":\"<h2>L\'azienda Poggio La Noce<\\/h2><p>\\r\\n\\t L\'azienda vitivinicola \\u00e8 stata fondata dai coniugi Enzo Schiano e Claire Beliard nel 2000. Immersa nelle colline di Fiesole, in Toscana, con esposizione a sud \\/ sud-ovest, la propriet\\u00e0 si trova in una delle pi\\u00f9 belle campagne alle porte di Firenze, tra colline cosparse di campanili medievali e castelli.<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t La propriet\\u00e0 comprende la vigna (2 ettari) coltivata con uve principalmente sangiovese e una piccola percentuale di Teroldego, in un misto di vitigni pi\\u00f9 vecchi (oltre 15 anni) e vitigni pi\\u00f9 giovani (oltre 8 anni). Il vigneto grazie alle sue dimensioni ridotte viene curato in modo maniacale, rendendolo un vero e proprio gioiello.<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t  La nostra azienda e\' stata concepita sin dall\'inizio per la produzione rigorosamente biologica con la certificazione biologica conseguita gia\' nel 2006.<\\/p><h2>Il nostro team<\\/h2><p>I coniugi Enzo Schiano e Claire Beliard sono i proprietari dell\'azienda Poggio la Noce e insieme condividono la passione e la visione di creare dei grandi vini. Roberto corti, che lavora presso l\'azienda, ha studiato agronomia all\'universita\' di Firenze e gestisce tutto il lavoro relativo al vigneto e alla cantina, e contribuisce allo sviluppo dei vini con Enzo e Claire. Tutto questo sotto l\'attentissima tutela di Marcellino, il nostro adoratissimo pastore maremmano.<\\/p><p>Il nostro team di consulenti comprende Valentino Ciarla, il nostro tecnico ed enologo, Stefano Dini e Gianluca Grassi, i nostri consulenti agronomi.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"12\":[\"63\"],\"6\":\"Ulteriori informazioni sull\'azienda\"}}', '2015-04-02 06:59:16', '2015-04-02 06:59:16', '7c73b77d-4b16-4902-b15e-a323c4b82c80'),
